## 📝 Project Report

For this task, I designed a **Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic** using **Canva**. I chose this tool because its **drag-and-drop interface** made it easy to combine educational content with an attractive and professional visual layout.

My infographic was structured around **three major themes**:

- **What Digital Literacy Means**
- **Useful Digital Tools for Students**
- **Safe Internet Practices**

To make the design visually appealing, I used a **textured paper-style background**, which gave the poster a more polished and creative appearance. I also placed a **3D-style central illustration** to connect the different content sections and improve the visual flow of the infographic.

One of the most interesting things I learned while making this infographic was the importance of **visual hierarchy**. I understood how changes in **font size, weight, spacing, and underlining** can help guide the viewer’s attention more effectively.

The most challenging part of the design process was managing **negative space**. I had to make sure the infographic looked **clean and uncluttered** while still including enough useful information for students.

Overall, this task helped me improve both my **digital awareness** and my **basic design presentation skills**.

